messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /printshops/requests/{id}

- All methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping, so the controller methods use the paths exactly as declared. The path used in the two relevant methods is "/printshops/requests/{id}".
- Two controller methods explicitly map that path:
  - changeStatusPrintShopRequests(...) is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/requests/{id}", method = RequestMethod.POST) — so POST is explicitly supported.
  - getPrintShopRequest(...) is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/requests/{id}", method = RequestMethod.GET) — so GET is explicitly supported.
- No mapping exists that allows all HTTP methods, nor are there explicit mappings for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH in the source, so those are marked false. (Per your instructions, this determination is based solely on the code annotations, not on framework runtime behavior.)
